ZH: 我的下级员工非常勤奋。
EN: My subordinate employees are very diligent.

ZH: 行政部门的下级部门是人力资源部门。
EN: The subordinate department of the administration department is the human resources department.

ZH: 这个项目的负责人向她的下级传达了最新的指示。
EN: The project manager conveyed the latest instructions to her subordinates.

ZH: 我从下级那里得到了一些建议。
EN: I received some suggestions from my subordinates.

ZH: 这位总经理非常尊重和信任他的下级。
EN: The general manager respects and trusts his subordinates.

ZH: 我的下级正在做一项重要的调查。
EN: My subordinate is conducting an important investigation.

ZH: 这个部门的下级部门是市场营销部门。
EN: The subordinate department of this department is the marketing department.

ZH: 这位领导非常理解和支持下级员工。
EN: The leader understands and supports the subordinate employees.

ZH: 我的下级在会议上提出了一些很好的建议。
EN: My subordinate made some good suggestions at the meeting.

ZH: 这位总监对下级所做的工作不满意。
EN: The director is not satisfied with the work done by his subordinates.

ZH: 下级员工应该服从上级的指示。
EN: Subordinate employees should obey the instructions of their superiors.

ZH: 部门主管给下级员工分发了新任务。
EN: The department supervisor assigned new tasks to the subordinates.

ZH: 这个项目的下级责任包括调查和数据收集。
EN: The subordinate responsibilities of this project include investigation and data collection.

ZH: 这位经理对他的下级持有很高的期望。
EN: The manager has high expectations for his subordinates.

ZH: 我的下级们都很有能力和经验。
EN: My subordinates are all capable and experienced.

ZH: 这个团队的协作关系很好，上级和下级之间互相支持。
EN: The team has a good collaborative relationship, with support between superiors and subordinates.

ZH: 我们需要建立一个有效的上级和下级之间的沟通渠道。
EN: We need to establish an effective communication channel between superiors and subordinates.

ZH: 这个部门的下级员工需要完成特定的任务。
EN: The subordinates of this department need to complete specific tasks.

ZH: 上级和下级之间应该建立互信关系。
EN: Trust should be established between superiors and subordinates.

ZH: 下级员工的发展和成长对组织的发展也很重要。
EN: The development and growth of subordinates are also important for the organization's development.
